== Dinner: Crispy Chicken Schnitzel ==

Wash and dry all produce. Halve @lemon{1}; cut one half into wedges. Trim, then
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Cut @Yukon Gold
potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes, then place in a large #pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, about
~{15%minutes}. Meanwhile, stir together @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup} and
@fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} on a large #plate{}. Season with plenty of
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Pat @chicken cutlets{20%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}.

Brush two pieces of chicken with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} (1 packet). Coat
chicken in panko mixture, pressing to adhere. Set aside. Take remaining chicken
and season all over with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a
large pan over medium-high heat. Add barbecue chicken and cook until browned
on surface and no longer pink throughout, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Remove from
pan, store in a #reusable container{}, and refrigerate overnight.

Once potatoes are tender, reserve 1/2 cup cooking water, then drain well. Place
scallion whites and @butter{1%tablespoon} in empty pot. Cook over low heat
until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add potatoes and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon} (1 pack) and
reserved cooking water as needed to create a creamy consistency. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep on low heat, stirring occasionally, until meal is
ready.

Heat ¼-inch layer of oil in pan used for barbecue chicken. Once hot, add
breaded chicken to pan in a single layer. Cook until panko is crisp and chicken
is no longer pink throughout, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a
paper towel-lined #plate{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Discard oil and
wipe pan with a paper towel.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and season with plenty of @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, tossing, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in juice from
lemon half, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and half the scallion greens. Cook until
fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide potatoes
and cabbage between plates. Arrange breaded chicken alongside, garnish with
remaining scallion greens, and serve with lemon wedges on the side.

== Sandwich Lunch ==

> The Sandwich Lunch: Calories: 660, Fat: 37g, Saturated Fat: 14g, Carbohydrate:
> 47g, Sugar: 10g, Fiber: 1g, Protein: 39g, Cholesterol: 195mg, Sodium: 1660mg.
> The dinner's nutrition facts are separate (890 kcal).

In the morning, split @brioche buns{2} (toast if desired). Slice @dill pickle{1}
into thin rounds. Mix @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, ranch seasoning, and remaining
sour cream in a small #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread
mixture onto buns, then fill each with barbecue chicken, @cheddar cheese{2%slice},
and pickle slices. Wrap in #plastic wrap{} or #foil{} and pack each with
@hot sauce{2%teaspoon}. Drizzle with hot sauce before enjoying.

> TIP: If desired, remove chicken and microwave separately until hot.